d-flex
Sets display: flex;. The element becomes a flex container. Its direct children become flex items. Flexbox enables dynamic alignment, distribution, and resizing along axes.

flex-column
Changes the flex direction to vertical: flex-direction: column;.
Default flex direction is row (horizontal). This forces children to stack top-to-bottom.

flex-shrink-0
Sets flex-shrink: 0;.
Normally, flex items can shrink when space is limited. This prevents shrinking. The element keeps its width/height even if the parent is tight. Often used for sidebars.

p-3
Adds padding on all sides. In Bootstrap spacing scale, 3 = 1rem (usually 16px).
Equivalent to padding: 1rem;

bg-body-tertiary
Applies a contextual background color from Bootstrap’s theme variables.
“tertiary” is a subtle background shade, usually lighter than primary surfaces. It adapts to light/dark mode automatically.

